<h4>I have more than one child.  How do I register both on the same account?</h4>
<p>
	Our online registration does not allow more than one child to be registered on the same account.  Each individual
	member will need to create their own account.
</p>

<h4>Is parent/guardian information required?</h4>
<p>
	Yes, if the member is under the age of 18, parent/guardian information is required.
</p>

<h4>What if I am a member of multiple clubs?</h4>
<p>
	If you have two or more club affiliations, please contact USSA offices and we'll be happy to add additional clubs to your record.
</p>

<h4>Do I have to be affiliated with a club?</h4>
<p>
	No, you do not.  Some members choose to compete independently and are not affiliated with a club.
</p>

<h4>How do I know which division I am in?</h4>
<p>
	Your division is determined by your club's division, or the state where you do most of your training and competing.
</p>

<h4>Do I need primary medical insurance?</h4>
<p>
	USSA provides secondary accident insurance at USSA sanctioned events to those who provide their primary medical insurance
	information.  If you do not hold primary medical insurance, you will need to complete a Medical Exception Agreement.
	This agreement removes a member from coverage under USSA's secondary accident insurance and leaves the member solely
	responsible for all medical expenses incurred in connection with any USSA event or activity.
</p>

<h4>Does USSA keep my payment information on file?</h4>
<p>
	No, USSA's system does not maintain any payment information.  Payment information will be required for each transaction.
</p>

<h4>How do I get a new membership card?</h4>
<p>
	USSA charges $10 for a replacement card.  Please contact USSA Member Services at (435) 647-2666 or email
	membership@ussa.org with a Visa or MasterCard for payment.  Cards take 1-2 weeks to arrive, but you may print a
	membership verification from our website to use in the meantime.
</p>

<h4>Who is required to undergo a background screening?</h4>
<p>
	All coaches, officials and volunteers are required to undergo a background screening.  For more information regarding background
	screenings, please see our website: Note: http://ussa.org/magnoliaPublic/ussa/en/formembers/membership/backgroundscreening.html
</p>

<h4>Who can compete in Masters events?</h4>
<p>
	You may compete in Master's events if you hold an Alpine Master membership, or are 18-22 and hold an Alpine Student membership, or are over 18 with an Alpine Competitor membership.
	<br/>
	Note: Regional and National championships require an Alpine Master membership.
</p>

